Explanation

I inspected controllers/invoices.js. Two exported functions are implemented that handle POST requests to /invoices in this codebase:

- getInvoicesByUser reads req.query.searchQuery and returns a 200 JSON response with { data: invoices } where invoices is an array of invoice documents found by InvoiceModel.find({ creator: searchQuery }). On error it returns 404 with { message: error.message }.

- createInvoice reads req.body, constructs and saves a new InvoiceModel, and on success returns 201 with the newly created invoice object; on error it returns 409 with error.message.

Because both handlers are described as processing POST /invoices, the OpenAPI Operation documents both possible behaviors on the same operation: (a) query by searchQuery via query parameter returning 200 with data array, and (b) create a new invoice by sending a JSON request body returning 201 with the created invoice. The requestBody is left optional because the endpoint is used for querying as well; searchQuery is an optional query parameter. The schemas are kept generic (object / array of objects) because the InvoiceModel schema was not provided in the files you gave me. Error responses follow the shapes observed in the code: 404 returns an object { message: string }, while 409 returns the raw error.message (string).

